 on the potential sources of underlying instability, which basically are related to the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> budget deficit. And since they kind of all took it as given that the president was n't going to do anything on that one, they really could n't get an American commitment on that one, it was n't worth talking about.'' `` It does n't mean to say they wo n't be back about that question,'' he said, when they meet again in <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> with a new <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> president in office in 1989.
