<BYLINE>By SUSANNE M. SCHAFER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hudson </PERSON>, the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> attorney overseeing the Pentagon fraud probe, made his name fighting pornography, not corruption. He is known as `` an aggressive sort of guy'' who is n't averse to publicity At 41, <PERSON> Hudson </PERSON> is looking at perhaps his biggest case, the investigation into allegations that defense contractors and consultants bribed <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> officials for information to help win billions of dollars in contracts. He prides himself on `` quality prosecutions, and being firm and fair.'' Others say he is a dogged prosecutor, almost moralistic in his zeal. <PERSON> Hudson </PERSON> is the top federal attorney in northern <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>, where the Pentagon is located and where many of the consultants and contractors being investigated have offices. Although there is a special unit in the <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> that tracks down fraud, it appears that the case went to <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION> because it was too massive for the <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> unit to handle. Also, the unit's offices were located in northern <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>, within <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION>'s Just across the <LOCATION> Potomac </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> from the <LOCATION> Capitol </LOCATION>, the district traditionally has been a high-profile one for a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> attorney prosecuting federal cases. <PERSON> Hudson </PERSON> and his assistant, <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Aronica </PERSON>, will argue the cases for the government if any charges come to trial. `` There's a certain amount of prestige that comes with the turf. But <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> is an aggressive sort of guy,'' said <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Horan </PERSON>, the state attorney for <LOCATION> Fairfax </LOCATION> <LOCATIO