<DATELINE>SHIRLEY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A pet monkey named <PERSON> Bubba </PERSON> who escaped from a basement window and eluded police for three hours finally made a monkey out of everyone when he went home on his own, police said. The 2-foot-long spider monkey apparently escaped Thursday afternoon by tearing through a screen window, said <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> <PERSON> Droscoski </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Suffolk </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> police spokesman. The mischievous primate proceeded to shred the screens on neighbors' windows, and chased some of the neighborhood children, <PERSON> Droscoski </PERSON> said. When police arrived, <PERSON> Bubba </PERSON> mocked their efforts to capture him by jumping on top of the police car. A police emergency services unit tried to lasso him, but managed only to tree him in his own back yard. After about three hours, <PERSON> Droscoski </PERSON> said, `` he made a monkey out of everybody else. He decided to get back into the house through the same basement window.'' The monkey's owner was not at home at the time.
