to move. Most estimates of the Zocalo have been that at capacity it could hold as many as 1 million people. Spectators at Saturday's rally said the plaza, bordered by such landmarks as the National Palace and the Metropolitan Cathedral, clearly was filled to capacity and many were standing in surrounding streets. <ORGANIZATION> La </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jornada </ORGANIZATION>'s study found that a realistic estimate of a filled to capacity rally would be 194,865 people.
