e audio level that all of the original tapes produced by <PERSON> McClease </PERSON> were blank and that in their opinion the two reels looked fresh and never ... used.'' <PERSON> Mason </PERSON> and <PERSON> Sharpton </PERSON> have disavowed knowing <PERSON> McClease </PERSON> and suggested he is a government agent. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Attorney <PERSON> Rudolph </PERSON> <PERSON> Giuliani </PERSON> said the investigation into <PERSON> McClease </PERSON>'s allegations would continue, but he refused to say whether the government believes any recordings exist from wire-tapping of <PERSON> Mason </PERSON> and <PERSON> Maddox </PERSON>. `` I think it's appropriate at this point to say that any suggestion that the Rev. <PERSON> Sharpton </PERSON> was involved would be unfair,'' <PERSON> Giuliani </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Sharpton </PERSON> is under investigation by the <ORGANIZATION> Internal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revenue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> for failure to file income taxes and reportedly by a state grand jury for alleged personal use of charitable donations.
