<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Mubarak </PERSON> <PERSON> Awad </PERSON>, the American-Palestinian deported from <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> two weeks ago, urged Democrats on Saturday to call in their platform for `` a two-state'' solution in the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>. That would be `` a great victory,'' <PERSON> Awad </PERSON> said at a luncheon hosted by <PERSON> Margot </PERSON> <PERSON> Kidder </PERSON>, the actress and <PERSON> Jesse </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> activist, at the hotel where the <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Platform </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> was meeting. Awad, an advocate of civil disobedience, urged the Democrats to address the Palestinian plight in the party platform. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> deported <PERSON> Awad </PERSON> on June 13 after 40 days in custody and accused him of fomenting unrest on the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Awad </PERSON>, a Christian, said he was thinking of converting to <LOCATION> Judiasm </LOCATION> if that is the only way for him to get back into <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and his native <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Jesse </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> has sought to have the Democrats support a Palestinian homeland in their platform, but <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, the likely nominee, has resisted. The draft platform speaks of `` maintaining the special relationship with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'' while exerting `` new leadership to deliver the promise of peace and security through negotiations that has been held out to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and its neighbors by the Camp David Accords.'' Platform committee member <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Zogby </PERSON>, a <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> adviser and executive director of the <ORGANIZATION> Arab </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute <