s </PERSON> argued for `` democratic empowerment.'' He proposed spending $ 100 million to support black institutions in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>, such as trade unions and professional associations, to increase the power base of blacks. He criticized the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>'s decision that legalized abortion, saying that issue should be left to the public to decide.
