<HEAD>Energy Futures Close Lower</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: for Saturday PMs</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Profit-taking has ended a three-day rally in gasoline prices, while oversupply worries brought oil futures lower. July unleaded gasoline contracts fell 0.15 cent Friday to close at 50.91 cents a gallon on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. Gasoline prices fell back after having crossed the 51-cents-a-gallon level on Thursday. Traders, believing thatprice was too high, moved in to take profits, said <PERSON> Madison </PERSON> <PERSON> Galbraith </PERSON>, senior energy specialist with <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION>. Gasoline supplies remained tight in the Northeast, but that was not enough to extend the rally in the gasoline pit to a fourth day, said <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Beutel </PERSON>, assistant director of the energy group at <ORGANIZATION> Elders </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>. Meanwhile, futures prices for crude oil and home heating oil fell because of overabundant supplies, the analysts said. `` Any day that this market goes down, you can be sure someone somewhere is thinking, ` oversupply,''' <PERSON> Beutel </PERSON> said. The August contract for <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Intermediate </ORGANIZATION>, the benchmark <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> crude, fell 36 cents to close at $ 16.01 per 42-gallon barrel. The July contract for home heating oil dropped 0.80 cent to close at 43.14 cents a gallon.
